 and Irish: variant of   Mangan  ."]},{"name":"Mangan","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Ciaran, Declan.","Irish: from <b>Ó Maingín</b>, see   Mannion  .","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Mongáin</b> ‘descendant of <i>Mongán</i>’, a byname for someone with a luxuriant head of hair (from <i>mong</i> ‘hair, mane’)."]},{"name":"Mannings","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Donovan, Eamonn, Ronan.","Irish: variant of   Manning   1, with the addition of English excrescent <i>-s</i>."]}]},{"name":"Symon","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Usual English form of   Simeon  , borne in the New Testament by various characters: two apostles, a brother of Jesus, a Pharisee, a leper, a tanner, a sorcerer (who offered money for the gifts of the Holy Ghost, giving rise to the term <i>simony</i>), and the man who carried Jesus's cross to the Crucifixion."],"variants":[{"name":"Simen","meanings":["Usual English form of   Simeon  , borne in the New Testament by various characters: two apostles, a brother of Jesus, a Pharisee, a leper, a tanner, a sorcerer (who offered money for the gifts of the Holy Ghost, giving rise to the term <i>simony</i>), and the man who carried Jesus's cross to the Crucifixion."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":24,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Symon Manning II was born about 1235, in Kent, England. He had at least 3 sons with Tyraphena de Bettreds. He died after 1272."},"et":{"about 1235–after 1272":"umbes 1235–pärast 1272","1239–1286":"1239–1286","1270–1309":"1270–1309","1272–Male":"12